The paper deals with coding theory, specifically the construction of lexicodes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the properties of finite principal left ideal rings, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CR) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper presents a greedy algorithm for constructing lexicodes, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
